stories: In my opinion, there is an unequal distribution of State funds to its residents, especially those living in urban areas. Currently, only corporations pay State income taxes, while individuals do not. I have observed that State funding is used for various purposes, such as bicycle paths, road maintenance, defunct docks, and powerful politicians' pet projects, such as office buildings and state troopers. However, these funding and projects are not necessary within City limits. I was amazed at how much the State provides for City functions in larger cities, thus increasing the State budget. I saw on TV last night how the Arkansas Game and Fish Commission was showing children how to ice fish, but couldn't the parents do that? Yes, I pay property taxes, but I guarantee that if City residents had to pay for all the services they receive from the State, they would not be as wasteful. For example, on the office building, why not rent the space needed instead of building a new one, and help the office rental market? In my previous business, I would ask my managers, "How do you stop spending money?"
